Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.40,0:44:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,lead to altered states of consciousness.\NSo the other thing about a lot of these
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.48,0:45:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,trainings especially short ones\Nis um what they induce is an altered
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.04,0:45:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,state of consciousness but that is not a\Nspiritual dimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.31,0:45:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh you can go to the Monroe Institute\Nwhich I did spend 10 days laying on your
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.28,0:45:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,back with earphones on both ears and\Nlearn how to leave the body at will and
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.48,0:45:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,meet people in various astral domains\Netc.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.28,0:45:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But that is an altered state of\Nconsciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.48,0:45:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is also feedback machines etc. So you\Ncan go into alpha alpha mode training
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.96,0:45:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and various things like that. Those are\Naltered states of consciousness that is
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.52,0:45:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,not a spiritual condition. It's an\Naltered state of consciousness which can
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.11,0:45:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,be learned and which is usually sold by\Ntrainings
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.44,0:45:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,for which you pay money.\NWhat I'm describing is a fact resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.59,0:45:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. All right. Those are altered\Nstates of consciousness and it's not the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.40,0:46:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,same thing as spiritual awareness in\Nwhich these phenomena occur their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.40,0:46:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Sooner or later, you probably go out of\Nbody anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.11,0:46:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it's fun to learn how to do it\Nif you when you want. Yeah. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.16,0:46:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So, anyway, let's go to the\Nnext uh thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.28,0:46:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh what's the next slide? Um\Nwell, whatever it says.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.64,0:46:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, non-binding. There are no\Nregulations, laws, edicts, contracts, or
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.72,0:46:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,pledges.\NMake no pledges. Make no pledges.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.04,0:46:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There was the pledge\Nof a previous lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.68,0:46:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Three or four of us got together one\Ntime at a lecture all held up by and
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.92,0:46:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,then we took a photograph of all the\Nthumbless ones. We all blamed this
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.76,0:46:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,belong to the same cult\Nsame number of lifetimes ago
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.11,0:47:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,or may the so and so be my fate blood\Npledge can never leave etc. And if
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.72,0:47:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,should I leave, may that be my fate.\NReal did. Therefore, I say, make no
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.28,0:47:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,pledges, take no oaths because they're\Nbinding down through lifetimes. It may
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.88,0:47:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,be three or four lifetimes ago that you\Nmade the pledge, but that pledge is
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.11,0:47:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,binding through lifetimes. Let's just\Nmake sure we're correct about that. The
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.59,0:47:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,pledge you make is binding through\Nlifetimes. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.64,0:47:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It is binding through lifetimes. So some\Nof the phenomena that may happen to you
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.31,0:47:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,are a consequence of having made a\Npledge, a blood pledge at a certain
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.31,0:47:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,level of commitment and may the so and\Nso be my fate. Well, you will that you
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.04,0:47:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,said it. You put it out in the universe\Nand it's now part of your karmic
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.80,0:47:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,inheritance. Huh? So I say make no\Npledges. Make no pledges. Swear no
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.52,0:48:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,oaths. Make no pledges and swear no\Noaths.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.92,0:48:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It says that some place in the good book\Ntoo. Jesus or somebody said it. I forget
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.68,0:48:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,who said it. Somebody somebody said it.\NFreedom not participants are free to
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.20,0:48:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,come and go without uh persuasion or\Npersecution or retaliation or
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.80,0:48:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,intimidation.\NThere's no hierarchy, no officers.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.07,0:48:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody just does what they do\Nvoluntarily. And you can see all the
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.68,0:48:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,staff that works with us. They just do\Neverything they do voluntarily.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.83,0:48:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course under secret threat but\Nfew threats here and there carry a
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.88,0:48:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,little commonality\Nanyway all comes about as a consequence
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.64,0:48:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,of the advancement of this everybody's\Nown level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.55,0:49:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh truth avoids glamorization.\NIt it avoids seduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.88,0:49:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,uh theatrics or power over others. Why\Nwould anybody who's enlightened want
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.76,0:49:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,power over other people? Tell me that.\NAll what they're telling you if they
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.35,0:49:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,want power over other people is that\Nthey're not enlightened. If they're not
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.00,0:49:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,enlightened, then why be bothered\Ntreating them like a super guru?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.92,0:49:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would anybody want to control the\Nlife of somebody else?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.00,0:49:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're enlightened, you're complete\Nand total and sufficient unto yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.11,0:49:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no need to control others, the\Nglamour of control and all that. So
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.55,0:49:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the teacher is has a defect where\Nthey're vulnerable and the demons will
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.88,0:49:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,find that out the demons. And I've been\Nhit by demons throughout my periodically
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.07,0:49:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in my spiritual illusion. The Buddha\Ncomplained about them. Jesus complained
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.24,0:49:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,about them. Anyway, so the demons will\Nattack you as you progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.92,0:50:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like temptations will come up in an\Narea where the evil spirits
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.24,0:50:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,figure you got to\Nplace in your army they can get through.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.00,0:50:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Place in an armor to get through. They\Nlike fill you out to see where it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.96,0:50:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Do I still have to fight demons? Yes.\Nnegative attitude towards that which is
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.35,0:50:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,destructive, evil and sadistic. I have\Nto watch that my umbrage doesn't come up
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.88,0:50:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,about that like indignation.\NThe rape and murder of small children
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.68,0:50:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and dogs and things. I have to watch\Nthat the spiritual night
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.55,0:50:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't come up to me\Nand with a condemning attitude. See, so
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.04,0:50:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,wherever you are along the way, this is\Na tough book I'm writing right now. This
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.88,0:50:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is the toughest of all of them. I mean,\Ntruth versus falsehood was tough. This
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.55,0:51:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is even tougher.\NReality, spirituality, and modern man.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.96,0:51:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if you're going to write about\Nmodern man, you got to look at modern
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.48,0:51:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,man, which really primarily means the\Nmedia and politics and all this. And of
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.92,0:51:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,course, Jesus said, don't uh engage in\Nevil, avoid evil. So, I have to look at
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.16,0:51:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,evil. have to look at evil in order to\Nwrite about modern men.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.96,0:51:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Looking at evil brings up the energy of\Nevil. So Jesus Christ said, "Do not uh
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.48,0:51:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,fight evil. Avoid it. Avoid it." So even\Nto look at it has its consequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.35,0:51:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And uh I'm recovering from the\Nconsequences of having looked at it for
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.24,0:51:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,number of months\Nand I'm happily looking forward to
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.64,0:51:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,finishing the end the end of the book uh\Nbecause I don't even like witnessing it
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.28,0:51:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,witnessing it. All right.\NDetached. There is non-involvement in
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.80,0:52:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the world's affairs. You see uh you're\Nas detached as you can be and still, you
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.31,0:52:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,know, be what you are. benign.\NUh
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.88,0:52:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,truth is benign. It has no enemies. You\Nknow, there's nobody you have to
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.48,0:52:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,denounce. There's nobody you have to\Ndenounce. So instead you can see that um
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.76,0:52:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution is delayed and those people\Nwho fall way below 200
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.11,0:52:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,uh it's because of karmic propensities\Nand therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.76,0:52:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,uh everyone is actually innocent at a\Ncertain level. They're innocent on the
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.76,0:52:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,other hand they're also responsible.\NSo on the other hand, karmically you owe
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.44,0:52:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it, but as far as let's say guilt and\Nall, it's it's not a sin. On the other
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.00,0:52:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,hand, you still owe it. So you didn't\Nmean to kill somebody, but you still owe
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.40,0:53:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,a life. That's different than the karma\Nof murder where you purposely did kill
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.35,0:53:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody. That has different\Nconsequences. But if you took a life,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.07,0:53:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you owe a life. So\Nhowever, it's not a negative. It's just
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.48,0:53:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,a rebalance. Karmic rebalance. Okay.\NUhhuh. Non-intentional truth does not
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.31,0:53:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,intervene or have an agenda proposed to\Ninflict on others and to promulgate.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.96,0:53:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You know,\Nwe're not concerned if if if nobody
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.96,0:53:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,hears of the work we're doing and if\Nnobody practices it, it's fine with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.55,0:53:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NI mean, they got along fine without me
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.24,0:53:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and I got along fine without them. I\Nguess the world will survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.64,0:53:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Not as well. However, of course,\Nnon-intentional truth truth is not it
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.04,0:53:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,has no positions and doesn't want to do\Nanything to anybody. Non-dualistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.48,0:54:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. As we just mentioned, the karma is\Nintrinsic to the intention. So, we'll go
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.48,0:54:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to the next one. Has to do with\Nintention. Tranquility and peace. There
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.68,0:54:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,are no issues or participants.\Nuh laughter we say with there's a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.20,0:54:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,laughter and uh uh the everything is\Nhappening independently autonomous as a
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.11,0:54:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,consequence of that which it is\Nequality is a reverence for all of life
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.64,0:54:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and all of its expressions. Therefore,\Nyou see the holiness. I always notice
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.52,0:54:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the holiness\Nand the beauty of animal life. The
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.72,0:54:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,innocence of animal life is so stunning.\NUh because you don't get into human
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.55,0:54:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,positionalities about it. Now I have\Nsitting on my desk there's this doggy
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.92,0:54:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and here these doggy\Nand sitting on
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.11,0:55:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,sitting on top of this doggy is a kitty.\NNow here's the doggy sitting there like
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.00,0:55:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that. There's the kitty sitting there on\Ntop. If that doesn't knock you out, I
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.76,0:55:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,don't know what. It's hard to get to my\Nwork. I take a glance at him and it just
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.35,0:55:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of puts you in a bliss state. You\Nknow what I'm saying? You see the
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.40,0:55:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,uh what's called animal grace, divine\Nanimal grace, the grace of the animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.64,0:55:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you become more evolved, you pick\Nup the beauty of all of nature, the
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.20,0:55:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,grace of all all of animal life. And\Neventually even the grace of a human
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.72,0:55:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,life even though you may not be agreeing\Nwith it. I see the valor with which the
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.11,0:55:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,dedicated savage uh is savages and kills\Nothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.40,0:55:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh and I see I see his intention. Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.07,0:55:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Equality, you know, reverence for all of\Nlife and all of its expressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.20,0:55:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Life is realized to be eternal and\Nphysicality is only temporary and life
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.76,0:56:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is not subject to death. And the reason\Nthat for that is that the energy of life
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.16,0:56:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,like the conservation of matter and the\Nconservation of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.00,0:56:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,uh cannot be destroyed. Let's just\Nrevalidate that because that is
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.92,0:56:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,incredible. There's the\Nlife cannot be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.83,0:56:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. There's the principle of\Nindestructibility of energy. It can only
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.20,0:56:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,change form of matter. It can only\Nchange form. And life cannot be
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.88,0:56:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,destroyed. It can only change form. So\Nwhen you swat a moth, he goes right on
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.55,0:56:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,flying in his little ethereal astral\Nbody and doesn't even notice that he
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.68,0:56:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,swatted him. He doesn't even notice that\Nyou swatted him. You don't have to get
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.07,0:56:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,up.\NThe moth doesn't even notice it. You
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.16,0:56:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,just You don't even notice it. There you\Nare. Whoa. Poor poor moth. The moth
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.28,0:57:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't even notice it.\NSo there's irreverencing life does not
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.24,0:57:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,mean to become modelin. Sometimes you\Nsee modellinism and sentimentality
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.55,0:57:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and there sort of a wimpy uh business\Nabout it all. No, he doesn't even
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.44,0:57:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,realize it.\NAnytime I uh left the body, uh it just
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.35,0:57:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,happened spontaneously. Nobody asked me\Nif I wanted to.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.28,0:57:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, one second. You're in the body\Nand one second later you're not the
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.44,0:57:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,body. Do you agree the body? No.\NEvery time that happened to me, I looked
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.79,0:57:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,at the body. I had the slightest\Ninterest. Looks sort of stupidly there
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.24,0:57:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to tell you the truth. And you had to\Nsort of talk yourself into resuming it
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.00,0:57:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's not at all interesting. He\Nsay now here you spend all your life
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.16,0:57:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,valuing and calling it as me and now\Nthat you're not in it, it's worthless.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.00,0:57:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's a very strange thing, but it\Nis. The second you leave the body, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.07,0:58:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,totally uninteresting and totally\Nworthless. It's like a bag of dirty
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.07,0:58:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,laundry. I mean, you know, no appeal to\Nit. You say, "Well, it's not your turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.48,0:58:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Time to leave yet."\NNot time to leave yet. You got to go
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.64,0:58:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,back in. You say, "Ah,\Nyou watch. You'll see. You
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.40,0:58:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you say, "Ah,\Nno. It's not your time to leave now.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.52,0:58:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You're just going back there."\NCrying and whimpering won't do you any
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.48,0:58:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,good. You got 14 and a half more years\Non your karmic clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.88,0:58:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So, all right, back to work. Back to\Ntaking your lunch to the office.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.79,0:58:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Life is realized to be eternal. Uh\Nthat which is provable is linear. You
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.52,0:58:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot prove anything we do or say. Uh\Nyou can realize it. Uh you can
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.72,0:59:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,demonstrate it. You can confirm it. But\Nit does not belong to the provable. The
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.44,0:59:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,provable belongs to the linear domain of\Nthe 400s. You can prove things by logic
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.35,0:59:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and math. Uh you cannot prove love. You\Ncannot prove consideration. You cannot
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.59,0:59:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,prove grace or beauty. None of those\Nthings are provable. They're are
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.68,0:59:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,mystical.\NUh that which arises out of truth is an
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.55,0:59:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,eulgence, a radiance,\Nuh an illumination. So we say that
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.92,0:59:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,people who have advanced things are\Nilluminated. Why? Because the
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.24,0:59:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding of it arises from within.\NThat's the value of meditation and
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.35,0:59:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,contemplation. With contemplation, then\Nyou begin to see a recontextualization
